Saudi Arabia Awards $267 Million in Water Contracts, SPA Says

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-03-16T14:09:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/saudi-arabia-awards-267-million-in-water-contracts-spa-says.html
  Saudi Arabia  awarded two contracts
valued at 1 billion riyals ($267 million) to Indian and Turkish
companies to transfer desalinated water produced from Ras Al
Zour station to Hafr Al Batin, the  Saudi Press Agency  reported,
citing Minister of Water and Electricity Abdullah al-Hussayen.  The news service did not identify the companies.  The Indian company won a 298.6 million riyal contract to
produce and supply steel pipes while a Turkish group of
companies won a 708.7 million riyal contract to transfer and
pump water, SPA said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  